Fast food chain, Domino’s Pizza  has reduced the price of pizza with the launch of the everyday value range pizzas. The recent development is in response to the continuous increase in the cost of living in the country and the grappling market force of inflation. To this end, Domino’s Pizza Nigeria has stepped up plans to redefine enjoyment with the launch of Everyday Value Range Pizza for N2,500 to enable consumers fix their affordability and make demands for pizza. The new pizza range is available across all Domino’s pizza branches nationwide for just N2500 with 7 new exciting flavours. The company, in a statement to LEADERSHIP, said, “this is pure enjoyment, at a super affordable price, but it is also unsurprising as we know that Domino’s Pizza, the #1 pizza chain in the country, loves to innovate and give it’s customers value for their money, from local to international flavour to different range of pizzas and multiple offerings.” The company added that, it recently launched the 20mins delivery time guarantee, and now they have redefined affordable enjoyment with the launch of their new everyday pizza range to satisfy consumers with affordable price. Meanwhile, this new pizza range is specially created for all to better enjoy their wonderful pizza moments with exciting flavours namely: Cheese, Fiery Chic, Chickenpie, Fiery Beef, Meatball, Plantain Suya, and Smokey Sausage. The company added that, having a mouth-watering flavour and belly filling pizza at the price of N2,500 in this economy is something wonderful and truly exciting which speaks on the epitome of Domino’s giveaway prices as it launches value range pizzas.